# Leave this UNSET (or set to /api) to use the built-in Next.js proxy in
# next.config.js, which forwards requests server-to-server to the real
# backend and avoids browser CORS issues entirely.
#
# Only set this to the backend's full URL directly if its CORS config has
# been updated to allow your domain — then the proxy becomes unnecessary.
